COP5570 Project 4
Grant Gibson
4/16/2026



1. ===== COMPILE =====
run "make"
server at ./bin/ttt_server



2. ===== RUN =====
./bin/ttt_server <port>
Connect with telnet: telnet linprog# <port>



3. ===== DEMO =====
Start the server on a linprog machine
Open three telnet sessions

Session 1:
    - Login as guest, register a new user (e.g. "alice")
    - Logout, login as alice

Session 2:
    - Login as guest, register a new user (e.g. "bob")
    - Logout, login as bob

Session 3:
    - Login as guest, register a new user (e.g. "joe")
    - Logout, login as joe

exit, quit
    alice: exit
    alice: quit

tell
    alice: tell bob hello bob
    alice: tell blank hello (will deny)

shout
    alice: shout hello all

help, ?
    alice: help or ?

who
    alice: who
    bob: exit
    alice: who (bob gone)

stats
    alice: stats bob

block, unblock
    alice: block bob
    bob: tell alice hi
    bob: shout alice hi
    bob: match alice

quiet, nonquiet
    alice: quiet
    bob: shout hello
    bob: tell alice hello

mail/listmail
    alice: mail bob hello\n test email\n .
    bob: listmail

readmail
    bob: readmail 1
    bob: listmail (marked as read)

deletemail
    bob: deletemail 1
    bob: listmail (gone)

match:
    alice: match bob w 20
    bob: match alice w 300
    alice: match bob b 300 (game starts)

observe, unobserve, game
    (match between alice and bob)
    joe: game (get game id)
    joe: observe 1
    joe: unobserve

resign (5)
    (match between alice and bob)
    alice: resign (bob wins)

kibitz (’), refresh (5)
    (match between alice and bob)
    alice: ' hello observers
    joe: kibitz hello other observers
    joe: refresh
    alice: refresh

game play (move, time) (10)
    (match between alice and bob)
    alice: A1
    bob: A3
    alice: A1 (not allowed)
    bob: C1 (not your move)
    alice runs out of time: bob wins on time

info:
    alice: info hello i am alice
    bob: stats alice

passwd:
    alice: passwd 1234
    alice: logout
    login: alice
    password: 1234 (works)



4. ===== POSSIBLE BUG =====
- Time is only checked at the start of each move, not in real time. A player
  who runs out of time will not lose until next move. If the player who runs
  out of time makes a winning move overtime the server still registers it as
  a loss. I am not sure if timing moves in real time is required.



5. ===== AI USAGE =====
AI tools were used as a programming assistant throughout this project.
AI was used to help understand implimenting socket programming concepts 
such as select() and debugging many issues catching subtle copy-paste errors, 
and to suggest code structure such as class and struct layouts. All code was 
written, reviewed, and understood by me. No submitted code was directly 
generated by AI.



